--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, AzureDamselfly &lt;azuredamselfly@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; Hi!
&gt;  
&gt; It happens always at night and at different times during the day. Rain, shine, snow does not matter. Today the diningroom lights were turning off and on, we have new electrical and did all of those checks necessary. 
&gt;  
&gt; The pattern recently is this: We go to bed . We may or may not see a dark shadow move in the bedroom. Within 10 minutes the banging begins. It sounded last night as if things were being thrown on the floor on my side of the bed. Nothing had fallen. Then it moves all around the room hitting the mirrorred door, the tv, the next wall, then Jay&#39;s bedside table and ends with the window above our heads. A full circle. We told it to go. It got quiet for 4 hours. Usually it just continues and gets louder. It also seems to like banging the door and all 4 walls of the closet. I have been sleeping with a fan on to drown it out and as a result it has gotten much louder. 
&gt;  
&gt; HAha as I type this it is banging behind my head on the china cabinet. When I came downstairs early this a.m. it banged 3 walls, in succession, as loudly as it could not 2 feet behind me. It is now banging on the case of my PC, my monitor, the dinigroom table and the ceiling...brother, it never gives up.  It walks up and down the stairs, scars the bejeezuz outta our 14 yr old cat, bangs the front door, the porch ceiling and walks overhead in the attic over the 2nd floor bedroom. 
&gt;  
&gt; We know the other spirits who reside with us, this one we don&#39;t. Oh yes, sometimes we get a very foul odor associated with it. ( heavy testosterone/ chicken soup/ dirty sweatsocks smells) Other times we smell heavy Old Spice over our faces in the bed.
&gt;  
&gt; It also seems to thrive on negativity. We work very hard to contain that in our home, the negativity I mean. If Jay & I have an argument it REALLY gets active. Makes us wonder if moving is the solution.
&gt;  
&gt; BTW, we have so many EVP&#39;s it isn&#39;t funny. One of my deceased son, Jay&#39;s Dad, and something very garbled. The one of my son is VERY clearly stating his name. THAT was the best! 
&gt;  
&gt; Keep the ideas and suggestions coming, please! 
&gt;  
&gt; Thanks much! 
&gt; Annie & Jay C.
&gt;  
&gt; I appreciate your response. Where is MAPS located?
